---
import MainLayout from '../../layouts/MainLayout.astro';

const BASE_URL = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const currentURL = `${BASE_URL}legal/accessibility-statement`;

const breadcrumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', url: BASE_URL },
  { name: 'Legal', url: `${BASE_URL}legal/` },
  { name: 'Accessibility Statement', url: currentURL }
];
---

<MainLayout
  title="Accessibility Statement | Marketing AI Houston"
  description="Marketing AI Houston's commitment to web accessibility. Learn about our WCAG 2.1 Level AA conformance efforts and how to report accessibility issues."
  canonicalURL={currentURL}
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
>
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-gradient-to-b from-ocean-50 to-white py-12 sm:py-16 lg:py-20">
    <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-xl p-6 sm:p-8 lg:p-12">
        <header class="mb-8 border-b border-ocean-100 pb-6">
          <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-ocean-900 mb-4">
            Accessibility Statement
          </h1>
          <p class="text-sm text-ocean-600">
            <time datetime="2025-10-06">Last updated: October 6, 2025</time>
          </p>
        </header>

        <div class="prose prose-ocean prose-lg max-w-none">
          <p class="lead">We are committed to making Marketing AI Houston accessible to everyone, including people with disabilities. This Accessibility Statement explains our approach, current conformance status, work in progress, and how to contact us about accessibility issues.</p>

          <section>
            <h2>Conformance status</h2>
            <p><strong>Current status:</strong> Partial conformance with WCAG 2.1 Level AA.</p>
            <p>We have taken steps to follow accessibility best practices across our website but are still working toward full conformance.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2>What we have done so far</h2>
            <ul>
              <li>Implemented semantic HTML, logical heading structure, and meaningful link text.</li>
              <li>Added accessible form labels, error messaging, and keyboard‑navigable controls.</li>
              <li>Implemented skip links and ensured focus styles for interactive elements.</li>
              <li>Checked color contrast for primary interface elements to meet AA contrast ratios.</li>
              <li>Used accessible patterns for navigation and responsive layouts to support keyboard and screen reader users.</li>
              <li>Included alt text for key images and ensured decorative images are marked so assistive technologies ignore them.</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2>Known limitations and planned improvements</h2>
            <p>Some legacy content and third‑party embeds may not fully meet WCAG 2.1 AA; we are auditing and prioritizing fixes.</p>
            <p>Dynamic content generated by certain third‑party tools may need improved ARIA support.</p>
            <p>We plan periodic accessibility testing, including manual keyboard and screen reader testing, and to address issues on a prioritized schedule.</p>

            <h3>Planned next steps:</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Complete a site-wide accessibility audit and remediation plan.</li>
              <li>Improve ARIA attributes for dynamic elements and third‑party widgets.</li>
              <li>Add automated checks to our CI pipeline and schedule quarterly manual testing.</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2>Reporting accessibility problems</h2>
            <p>If you encounter accessibility barriers on our site, please let us know by contacting us:</p>
            <address class="not-italic mb-4">
              Email: <a href="mailto:team@marketingaihouston.com">team@marketingaihouston.com</a>
            </address>

            <p>When reporting, please include:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>The page URL (or screenshot) where you experienced the issue.</li>
              <li>A description of the problem and the assistive technology or browser you used.</li>
              <li>Your contact information if you'd like us to follow up.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>We will respond within 5 business days and provide an estimated timeline for remediation when possible.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2>Technical specifications</h2>
            <p>This site follows WCAG 2.1 Level AA as a target standard. The accessibility work referenced above uses common techniques from ARIA, semantic HTML, and responsive design. Where applicable, our development and QA processes reference the W3C techniques and best practices.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2>Compatibility and testing</h2>
            <p>The site is tested on modern browsers (Chrome, Firefox, Edge, Safari) and on common screen readers (NVDA, VoiceOver).</p>
            <p>We aim to support keyboard navigation and zoom/text-size adjustments up to 200% without loss of content or functionality.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2>Accessibility statement for third-party content</h2>
            <p>Some embedded or linked third‑party content may have different accessibility levels. We strive to select third parties with robust accessibility practices and will work with partners to address issues.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2>Enforcement procedure and legal rights</h2>
            <p>This statement is intended to describe our accessibility efforts and provide a path to report barriers. It is not a contract or legal guarantee. If you require formal accommodations or have legal questions, please contact us at <a href="mailto:team@marketingaihouston.com">team@marketingaihouston.com</a>.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2>Updates to this statement</h2>
            <p>We will update this Accessibility Statement as our site evolves and remediation work is completed. The "Last updated" date above reflects the most recent revision.</p>
          </section>
        </div>

        <footer class="mt-12 pt-6 border-t border-ocean-100">
          <nav class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 text-sm text-ocean-600">
            <a href={`${BASE_URL}legal/terms-of-service`} class="hover:text-ocean-800 underline">Terms of Service</a>
            <a href={`${BASE_URL}legal/privacy-policy`} class="hover:text-ocean-800 underline">Privacy Policy</a>
            <a href={`${BASE_URL}legal/cookie-policy`} class="hover:text-ocean-800 underline">Cookie Policy</a>
            <a href={`${BASE_URL}legal/copyright-notice`} class="hover:text-ocean-800 underline">Copyright Notice</a>
          </nav>
        </footer>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</MainLayout>

